comments.text:
This is insane and not understandable at all. Given that we cache the tab id I would have expected to see at least only improvements but no regressions.

On the other hand there is the other patch for opening a new tab only when the test actually requests it:
https://hg.mozilla.org/integration/autoland/rev/07408b255fec

I wonder which effect this actually has, and if there is something wrong with picking up the correct start time. We could temporarily back this out and properly investigate what's broken afterward. I just pushed try build with the backed out patch:

https://treeherder.mozilla.org/#/jobs?repo=try&revision=80e7ae5fb058f38dc446f87fcfb4503f0cca9732
